{"id": "112139fe8b10", "text": "Use templates/accessibility-audit/ for all audit reports. Each finding must include: component or page location, WCAG 2.2 success criterion number and name, current behavior, expected behavior, severity rating, and remediation steps with code example.", "domain": "ux.accessibility", "agent_source": "accessibility-auditor", "type": "preference", "confidence": 0.667, "source": "accessibility-auditor.md:31", "embedding_idx": 5, "first_seen": "2026-03-21", "last_validated": "2026-03-21", "status": "active", "evidence": {"accepted": 0, "rejected": 0, "modified": 0}, "projects_seen": [], "tags": ["templates", "accessibility", "wcag"], "related_claims": []}
{"id": "ad114ea9f5cb", "text": "Never recommend ARIA when native HTML semantics suffice (first rule of ARIA). Test keyboard interaction in the order: Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, Escape, Arrow keys. Verify that all ARIA roles have required owned elements and required states. Confirm that dynamic content updates are announced to assistive technology via live regions or focus management.", "domain": "ux.accessibility", "agent_source": "accessibility-auditor", "type": "preference", "confidence": 0.667, "source": "accessibility-auditor.md:35", "embedding_idx": 6, "first_seen": "2026-03-21", "last_validated": "2026-03-21", "status": "active", "evidence": {"accepted": 0, "rejected": 0, "modified": 0}, "projects_seen": [], "tags": ["aria", "keyboard"], "related_claims": ["9c77b15edb1a"]}
{"id": "611948a73506", "text": "Always cite the specific law or heuristic supporting each recommendation. Prefer established conventions over novel interactions (Jakob's Law). Reduce choices when response time matters (Hick's Law). Make interactive targets large enough for reliable activation (Fitts's Law). Keep working memory demands within cognitive limits (Miller's Law). Provide system feedback within 400ms (Doherty Threshold).", "domain": "ux.interaction", "agent_source": "interaction-designer", "type": "preference", "confidence": 0.667, "source": "interaction-designer.md:22", "embedding_idx": 7, "first_seen": "2026-03-21", "last_validated": "2026-03-21", "status": "active", "evidence": {"accepted": 0, "rejected": 0, "modified": 0}, "projects_seen": [], "tags": [], "related_claims": []}
{"id": "a7700b61930a", "text": "Use templates/service-blueprint/ for blueprint deliverables. Use templates/journey-map/ for journey map deliverables.", "domain": "ux.service", "agent_source": "service-designer", "type": "preference", "confidence": 0.667, "source": "service-designer.md:17", "embedding_idx": 8, "first_seen": "2026-03-21", "last_validated": "2026-03-21", "status": "active", "evidence": {"accepted": 0, "rejected": 0, "modified": 0}, "projects_seen": [], "tags": ["templates"], "related_claims": []}
{"id": "d83e27a61171", "text": "Always include the line of visibility separating frontstage from backstage. Mark every point where the customer waits with a wait icon and expected duration. Mark every point where the service can fail with a fail icon and recovery plan. Connect frontstage actions to their backstage dependencies with clear arrows. Include time indicators: how long each phase takes from the customer's perspective.", "domain": "ux.service", "agent_source": "service-designer", "type": "preference", "confidence": 0.667, "source": "service-designer.md:21", "embedding_idx": 9, "first_seen": "2026-03-21", "last_validated": "2026-03-21", "status": "active", "evidence": {"accepted": 0, "rejected": 0, "modified": 0}, "projects_seen": [], "tags": [], "related_claims": []}
